{"https://hg.mozilla.org/mozilla-central/rev/400477da817caf193a069aab75fc886c7e6bd99f": {"commit_message": "Bug 1810810 - Add test for login preselection. r=mtigley,credential-management-reviewers\n\nDepends on D167259\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D177980", "push_date": "2023-05-23T09:47:12Z", "ranked_scenarios": [{"id": 1627627, "summary": "The \u201cAlerts\u201d option is not displayed in \u201cSort by:\u201d dropdown after syncing logins without refreshing the page if previously no breached/vulnerable were saved", "description": {"text": "Created attachment 9138490\nAlertsOptionIsNotDisplayedAfterSync.gif\n\n[Affected versions]:\n- Nightly 76.0a1 (Build ID: 20200405212522)\n\n[Affected Platforms]:\n- Windows 10 x64\n- Mac 10.14.6\n- Ubuntu 18.04 x64\n\n[Prerequisites]:\n- No vulnerable/breached accounts are displayed in the login list.\n- Have a Firefox Account with saved logins in which at least one is vulnerable and one is breached.\n\n[Steps to reproduce]:\n1. Open the Firefox browser with the profile from prerequisites.\n2. Navigate to the \u201cabout:logins\u201d page.\n3. Sign in to Sync with the Firefox Account from prerequisites.\n4. Click on the \u201cSort by:\u201d button.\n5. Observe the dropdown menu.\n\n[Expected result]:\n- The \u201cAlerts\u201d option is displayed on the dropdown.\n\n[Actual result]:\n- The \u201cAlerts\u201d option is not displayed on the dropdown.\n\n[Regression]\n-  The issue is not reproducible with older Nightly 76.0a1 builds. Considering this, using the mozregression tool I have found the issue that broke this in the latest Nightly build. Here are the results:\n - Pushlog: https://tinyurl.com/ss3vbj6.\n - Last good revision: 6e570f08779fae0699aec929011f3e0f8d668c33.\n - First bad revision: 4f97d7e79d15a71b12d268e1eb3967a79c3adaa9.\n\nFrom this pushlog it seems that Bug 1626413 introduced this behavior.\n\n[Notes]:\n- The \u201cAlerts\u201d option is displayed after refreshing the page.\n- This issue is not reproducible if I have breached/vulnerable logins saved in the profile before signing in to Sync.\n- Attached a screen recording with the issue.", "scenarios": null, "attachments": null}, "product_component_pair": {"product": "Firefox", "component": "about:logins", "description": null}, "tossing_path": {"product_component_pair_list": ["<Circular reference to ProductComponentPair object>"], "length": 1, "product_component_pair2idx": {"Firefox::about:logins": 0}}, "creation_time": "2020-04-06T09:53:37", "closed_time": "2020-04-11T09:37:37", "last_change_time": "2020-04-16T08:22:25", "status": "VERIFIED", "labels": ["defect"], "relation": {"bug_id": 1627627, "regressed_by": [1626413], "regressions": null, "blocks": [1565326], "depends_on": null, "duplicates": null, "see_also": ["https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=1628643"]}, "keywords": ["regression"], "attachments": [{"id": 9138490, "bug_id": 1627627, "summary": "AlertsOptionIsNotDisplayedAfterSync.gif", "description": "AlertsOptionIsNotDisplayedAfterSync.gif", "file_name": "AlertsOptionIsNotDisplayedAfterSync.gif", "content_type": "image/gif", "url": "https://bug1627627.bmoattachments.org/attachment.cgi?id=9138490"}, {"id": 9139581, "bug_id": 1627627, "summary": "Bug 1627627 - Show the 'Alerts' dropdown option if a login is vulnerable or breached login is added while the page is already open. r?MattN", "description": "Bug 1627627 - Show the 'Alerts' dropdown option if a login is vulnerable or breached login is added while the page is already open. r?MattN", "file_name": "phabricator-D70437-url.txt", "content_type": "text/x-phabricator-request", "url": "https://bug1627627.bmoattachments.org/attachment.cgi?id=9139581"}], "closer_pulls": [], "closed_issues": [], "crossref_issues": [], "crossref_pulls": [], "RANK": 1, "COUNT": 5}, {"id": 1561435, "summary": "Do a formatting pass on mozilla-central using Prettier (the actual change)", "description": {"text": "The actual formatting pass for bug 1558517\n\nIt's worth pointing out that this series becomes bitrotten on upload. These commits are useful for\n1. Dong a full formatting pass close to landing day and making sure we can address all known problems so far.\n2. Pinging the appropriate module owners and making sure they see what's going on.\n\nAs it stands, this final series serves as a guidance for that's probably extremely close to what's landing on July 5. Rebasing is not an option for generating these commits, which will be re-done.", "scenarios": null, "attachments": null}, "product_component_pair": {"product": "Developer Infrastructure", "component": "Lint and Formatting", "description": null}, "tossing_path": {"product_component_pair_list": [{"product": "Firefox Build System", "component": "Lint and Formatting", "description": null}, "<Circular reference to ProductComponentPair object>"], "length": 2, "product_component_pair2idx": {"Firefox Build System::Lint and Formatting": 0, "Developer Infrastructure::Lint and Formatting": 1}}, "creation_time": "2019-06-25T22:03:33", "closed_time": "2019-07-05T15:51:17", "last_change_time": "2023-08-27T02:51:01", "status": "RESOLVED", "labels": ["task"], "relation": {"bug_id": 1561435, "regressed_by": null, "regressions": [1633329, 1633969], "blocks": [1558517], "depends_on": null, "duplicates": [1559309], "see_also": null}, "keywords": null, "attachments": [{"id": 9073975, "bug_id": 1561435, "summary": "Bug 1561435 - Format devtools/client/, a=automatic-formatting", "description": "Bug 1561435 - Format devtools/client/, a=automatic-formatting", "file_name": "phabricator-D35884-url.txt", "content_type": "text/x-phabricator-request", "url": "https://bug1561435.bmoattachments.org/attachment.cgi?id=9073975"}, {"id": 9073976, "bug_id": 1561435, "summary": "Bug 1561435 - Fix linting errors for devtools/client/, r=standard8", "description": "Bug 1561435 - Fix linting errors for devtools/client/, r=standard8", "file_name": "phabricator-D35885-url.txt", "content_ty